  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "While statistical co-occurrence frequency is a useful measure for filtering out noisy correlations, it does not establish causation.",
    "For example, a material that is commonly used during a synthesis method and a material synthesized using that method will both have a high co-occurrence frequency for the material-synthesis method triple.",
    "However, the former is only a correlation, whereas the latter represents a true causal relationship.",
    "Even when there are strong correlations in the extracted triples, their precise relationship can still be different.",
    "For example, in MatKG both ('In2O3', 'Optical Material') and ('Bismuth', 'Nuclear Reactor') are connected by the relationship 'CHM-APL' indicating that the tuple connects a material to an application."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}